reviewText: Although I learned a lot about these amazing redwoods through this film, as a teacher in a Christian Homeschool Co-op, I was disappointed in some of the language.  No profanity was used that I caught, but inappropriate slang left me unable to show this film to our class which was quite disheartening.

reviewText: This movie has alot of information to process,multiple stories got to be blurry. What i mean is the info was great but jumping around between Researchers,Tree Protectors and Companies cutting them down. Then the Government stepping in buying the companies out.The story needs to be told but my thought it could've been edited differently.

reviewText: We expected to see pretty scenery in this DVD - but it was a real education about these amazing giants and their ecosystem.  We were quite surprised about how much we did not know about these breathtaking trees!  We will watch it again and share it with our friends.
summary: WOW!  This was a mini-education on the subject!

reviewText: We are planning our first trip to the Redwoods this summer.  We bought this video to give us an idea of what the lay of the land was.  We are hikers and wanted to see if it was going to be suitable for us.  Would have liked more "on the ground" pictures, but it was the only one available and it did the job.
